ync" width=3D"250" height=3D"188" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=
=3D"2592" data-file-height=3D"1944"></a><figcaption><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Croke_Park" title=3D"Croke Park">Croke Park</a> sports st=
adium in Dublin, Ireland. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pitc=
h_(sports_field)" title=3D"Pitch (sports field)">pitch</a> is used for <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaelic_football" title=3D"Gaelic footb=
all">Gaelic football</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hurling"=
 title=3D"Hurling">hurling</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Camogie" title=3D"Camogie">camogie</a>, and has also been used in the past=
 for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Association_football" title=
=3D"Association football">association football</a> and <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rugby_union" title=3D"Rugby union">rugby</a>. It has a=
 capacity of 82,300 people, making it the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/List_of_European_stadiums_by_capacity" title=3D"List of European st=
adiums by capacity">third largest stadium in Europe</a>.</figcaption></figu=
re>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croke_Park" title=3D"Croke Park=
">Croke Park</a> is the association's flagship venue and is known colloquia=
lly as <i>Croker</i> or <i>Headquarters</i>, since the venue doubles as the=
 association's base. With a capacity of 82,300, it ranks among the top five=
 stadiums in Europe by capacity, having undergone extensive renovations for=
 most of the 1990s and early 21st century. Every September, Croke Park host=
s the All-Ireland inter-county Hurling and Football Finals as the conclusio=
n to the summer championships. Croke Park holds the All-Ireland club footba=
ll and hurling finals. Croke Park is named after <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Croke" title=3D"Thomas Croke">Archbishop Thomas Croke=
</a>, who was elected as a patron of the GAA during the formation of the GA=
A in 1884.
</p><p>The Croke Park campus is also home to the <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/National_Handball_Centre" title=3D"National Handball Centre"=
>National Handball Centre</a>, which replaced the old Croke Park Handball C=
entre built in the 1970s. The centre is due to be the home of <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GAA_Handball" title=3D"GAA Handball">GAA Handba=
ll</a> and to play host to All-Ireland <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Gaelic_Handball" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Gaelic Handball">Gaeli=
c Handball</a> finals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaelic_Athletic_Association#cite_note-11"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Other_grounds">Other ground=
s</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGaelic_Ath=
letic_Association&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section:=
 Other grounds"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<p>The next three biggest grounds are all in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Munster" title=3D"Munster">Munster</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Semple_Stadium" title=3D"Semple Stadium">Semple Stadium</a=
> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thurles" title=3D"Thurles">Th=
urles</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_Tipperary" title=
=3D"County Tipperary">County Tipperary</a>, with a capacity of 53,000, the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaelic_Grounds" title=3D"Gaelic Gr=
ounds">Gaelic Grounds</a> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limer=
ick" title=3D"Limerick">Limerick</a>, which holds 50,000, and <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/P%C3%A1irc_U%C3%AD_Chaoimh" title=3D"P=C3=A1irc=
 U=C3=AD Chaoimh">P=C3=A1irc U=C3=AD Chaoimh</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/County_Cork" title=3D"County Cork">County Cork</a>, which c=
an accommodate 45,000.
</p><p>Other grounds with capacities above 25,000 include:
</p>
